While we were planning to look at a lot of different joysticks and
controllers all at one time, we've had trouble getting a wide variety of
controllers to compare all at the same time.  We've decided to feature a
new controller every month.

This month we've got a look at a new controller for the CD남

	@{"Competition Pro CD남 Controller" link CPSC} - The Review!!!

@ENDNODE

@NODE CPSC "Competition Pro Super CD남 Professional Control Pad"
The CD남 controller is one of the most comfortable controllers to hold in
your hands.  Unfortunately, it's not so good at withstanding the demands
of rugged gameplay.  Since that's what you need in a good controller, a
replacement controller that meets those demands is definitely in order.

Enter the Competition Pro Super CD남 Professional Control Pad.  (Actually,
they could have just called it "The Better One".)  This 10 button, Sega
Genesis style controller gets high marks for design, comfort and quality. 
It also adds a few little things that the original controller doesn't
have: Slow motion, auto-fire, turbo mode and a one year warranty.

The pad held up well while being tested.  It didn't make me score any
better, but I did feel like the controller was responding to my directions
better than the original CD남 controller.
 
I played MICROCOSM and CHAOS ENGINE for the tests.  I tried out the
auto-fire, turbo and slow motion.  The "features" proved to be more
gimmicky than actually useful.  CHAOS ENGINE didn't respond well to the
slow motion.  It merely turned the pause function on and off.  The
auto-fire worked, but turbo caused my character to spin to the right
non-stop.  MICROCOSM was a little better.  Everything worked fine, but it
didn't help me play any better.  The slow motion "feature" is a little
misleading.  It slows everything down, including you, so that it's no
easier to hit or do anything...you just do it a LOT slower.

The controller feels a lot sturdier than the regular CD남 controller.  I
felt a lot more in control of games with it than I ever did before.  The
original controller is far too mushy.  The Competition Pro is tight and
